mkdir — create directories

SYNOPSIS
  mkdir [-p] DIR...

DESCRIPTION
  Creates each named directory. With -p (parents) ancestor directories
  are created as needed and existing targets do not raise an error.

EXAMPLES
  mkdir new                    one directory in PWD
  mkdir -p /home/alex/cfg/x/y  full chain at once

EXIT STATUS
  0  all targets created (or already existed under -p)
  1  at least one target failed
  2  bad invocation

SEE ALSO
  rm(1), cp(1), mv(1), touch(1)
